231
00:12:10,634 --> 00:12:14,517
We could do something about that. We could make it so you know the bombs never overlap with the fruit.

232
00:12:14,537 --> 00:12:17,620
But it's deliberately has a little bit of overlap at least.

233
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,122
Because we want the game to be a little bit unfair.

234
00:12:20,922 --> 00:12:24,705
And the reason is, is in these games that are all about you know getting a high score

235
00:12:24,786 --> 00:12:27,488
and then retrying to get a high score again and again and again.

236
00:12:28,008 --> 00:12:29,710
By making the game a little bit unfair,

237
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:33,873
the player can assign some of the blame on their failure on the game.

238
00:12:34,583 --> 00:12:37,325
you know, rather than getting to 200 points and going, well,

239
00:12:37,845 --> 00:12:40,607
I'm never gonna beat that, I've reached my maximum skill limit.

240
00:12:40,987 --> 00:12:42,488
By making the game a little bit unfair,

241
00:12:43,349 --> 00:12:46,010
the player can go, well, if only that bomb wasn't there,

242
00:12:46,571 --> 00:12:50,413
if only I got that extra critical, if only, you know, all these scenarios.

243
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:54,575
They're placing some of the blame and, you know, some of the credit as well, to be sure,

244
00:12:54,855 --> 00:12:58,157
on the game itself rather than entirely on themselves, and it doesn't

245
00:12:58,718 --> 00:13:00,779
sting so much when you don't get the high score.

246
00:13:03,514 --> 00:13:06,796
So when you think about it, Fruit Ninja, classic mode at least,

247
00:13:07,597 --> 00:13:09,679
Monster Dash and Jetpack Joyride

248
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,642
don't seem like they're going to be a really good game for the player because

249
00:13:13,763 --> 00:13:16,765
effectively it's an inevitable march towards failure.

250
00:13:17,526 --> 00:13:18,287
There's no finish.

251
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:22,711
The end game for every game is failure on the player's behalf.

252
00:13:23,601 --> 00:13:29,305
So when you're doing a game like that, it's really important to make sure you fully understand what the costs of failure are.

253
00:13:29,785 --> 00:13:32,327
These for me are the three big costs of failure. Time lost,

254
00:13:32,847 --> 00:13:34,708
the feeling of failure, like the emotion,

255
00:13:35,449 --> 00:13:40,212
and the friction on starting again, or the retry loop, how long it takes to retry the game and get going again.

256
00:13:42,107 --> 00:13:44,807
So time lost, you know, changes a lot for different games.

257
00:13:44,847 --> 00:13:47,648
This is really vaguely organized, like on the left,

258
00:13:47,748 --> 00:13:50,289
from not much time lost to right, more time lost.

259
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:53,249
So, you know, Canabalt, if you're really shit like I am,

260
00:13:53,289 --> 00:13:55,990
your times are only like 10 seconds long.

261
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:57,391
So, you know, when you fail,

262
00:13:57,811 --> 00:13:59,091
it really doesn't hurt that much.

263
00:13:59,131 --> 00:14:00,331
You're ready to go again,

264
00:14:00,391 --> 00:14:02,432
and you can just keep going and going and going and going.

265
00:14:04,155 --> 00:14:09,577
even when they throw, you know, unfair situations at you like the glass window you have to jump in

266
00:14:09,697 --> 00:14:13,979
and the crazy car bomb thing that falls right in front of you, it doesn't hurt quite so much.

267
00:14:14,639 --> 00:14:19,622
On the other hand, you know, a game like Spelunky, you could be spending quite a long time on that before you die.

268
00:14:20,062 --> 00:14:24,904
And that, you know, you really feel it when you die in that game, you know,

269
00:14:24,984 --> 00:14:29,206
you scream at your monitor and all of that, which is fine, you know, for the game it is, that works perfectly,

270
00:14:29,266 --> 00:14:33,308
but especially on a mobile game, you want to be careful on how much time lost there is.

271
00:14:34,913 --> 00:14:38,154
There's also the emotional cost, so just how bad you feel.

272
00:14:38,194 --> 00:14:41,356
So if we just came up and as soon as you die in Jetpack it says,

273
00:14:42,417 --> 00:14:45,578
you failed and you're worthless as a human being.

274
00:14:46,139 --> 00:14:48,100
That's probably not a great way to treat the player.

275
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:52,042
So what we do with a lot of our games is we actually reward the player for failing.

276
00:14:52,762 --> 00:14:54,303
In Fruit Ninja, you know, when you...

277
00:14:55,047 --> 00:14:57,808
When you die when you hit a bomb in classic mode or drop the fruit

278
00:14:57,988 --> 00:15:00,169
We actually give you like a nice little fruit fact there

279
00:15:00,709 --> 00:15:06,831
You know gives you something to take your mind off the failure sensei's there. He's smiling at you like yeah, good job

280
00:15:06,851 --> 00:15:10,933
So you know we do a lot of things to minimize the emotional cost

281
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:14,890
In Jetpack Joyride we took this to the extreme.

282
00:15:15,290 --> 00:15:18,691
So you know, you die and then you have the slot machine.

283
00:15:18,711 --> 00:15:21,672
So like a whole nother mini game of prizes and excitement.

284
00:15:21,972 --> 00:15:23,372
And then even on the results screen

285
00:15:23,412 --> 00:15:25,273
we have the little Polaroid photo of you

286
00:15:25,293 --> 00:15:26,713
that gives you something to focus on.

287
00:15:27,053 --> 00:15:28,454
You got the leaderboards to check out.

288
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:30,274
You know, you're getting all of this kind of

289
00:15:30,394 --> 00:15:33,135
positive feedback and all this recognition for your game.

290
00:15:33,695 --> 00:15:36,616
If you get new best, then stuff pops up as well.

291
00:15:37,296 --> 00:15:39,136
We really do a lot of steps to minimize

292
00:15:39,156 --> 00:15:40,417
the emotional cost to the player.

293
00:15:41,957 --> 00:15:45,799
There's even this thing we do where, originally, when you ran into a zapper,

294
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:48,700
Barry just vaporized instantly. He just went, poof!

295
00:15:49,441 --> 00:15:51,222
And that was it. That was your score that you got.

296
00:15:52,362 --> 00:15:56,004
What we found by, you know, changing it so that he kind of, you know, gets zapped,

297
00:15:56,044 --> 00:16:00,726
and he bounces along and slides on his face, and sometimes he bounces and picks up a few coins,

298
00:16:00,786 --> 00:16:05,048
and if you're really lucky, you know, maybe you might pick up a spin token or something else along the way,

299
00:16:05,168 --> 00:16:08,950
or even complete a mission sometimes when you just need those extra few meters.

300
00:16:09,955 --> 00:16:12,476
is it almost fades in the failure

301
00:16:13,256 --> 00:16:15,678
rather than just being instantaneous, boom, you have failed.

302
00:16:16,178 --> 00:16:18,979
I mean, you take the hit, you know you've taken the hit and you've failed,

303
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:21,180
but instead of immediately considering

304
00:16:22,061 --> 00:16:23,081
the fact that you've failed,

305
00:16:23,642 --> 00:16:26,323
you have this little mini thing, it's only like two seconds or so long,

306
00:16:26,363 --> 00:16:29,004
but you're watching Barry bounce, you're kind of anticipating,

307
00:16:29,044 --> 00:16:30,945
trying to figure out whether he's gonna, you know,

308
00:16:31,005 --> 00:16:33,987
run into that next zapper or collect that coin or that token.

309
00:16:34,347 --> 00:16:36,688
And it almost fades in the failure in a way.

310
00:16:39,251 --> 00:16:48,568
The other stuff that we do is, you know, obviously, if you completed a mission, boom, you know, there's stars and explosions and coins and, you know, we do a lot to really try and make the player feel good about themselves.

311
00:16:48,949 --> 00:16:50,632
Come back to the mission system a little bit later.

312
00:16:51,964 --> 00:16:54,506
So the other one is restart friction as well.

313
00:16:55,287 --> 00:17:00,371
So when I say restart friction, I mean like how difficult is it for the player to restart the game?

314
00:17:00,852 --> 00:17:03,034
You know, how seamless does it feel?

315
00:17:03,774 --> 00:17:10,300
So in Jetpack, you'll notice I have, this is kind of like a comic book, so you start at the top left and read across.

316
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:16,503
When the final spin machine comes up, instead of cutting abruptly to a whole different screen,

317
00:17:16,963 --> 00:17:23,347
we actually kind of simultaneously slide the machine up and fade the game in the background down,

318
00:17:23,387 --> 00:17:25,588
but the game in the background is always there.

319
00:17:26,102 --> 00:17:31,585
So rather than kind of cutting to a whole nother area, you're still being, you know, you're still within the game world.

320
00:17:32,026 --> 00:17:37,449
And it just kind of makes it feel a bit more seamless and, you know, rather than kind of cutting out to a whole nother room.

321
00:17:38,229 --> 00:17:41,791
Even then when we slide the final spin off, you'll see the game is still in the background.

322
00:17:42,092 --> 00:17:45,434
We mess around with the tint of it a bit just so that it doesn't conflict with the menus.

323
00:17:46,594 --> 00:17:51,817
And, you know, the other thing is, is we always make sure that restarting is as easy as possible.

324
00:17:52,198 --> 00:17:53,678
So in the final spin, if...

325
00:17:54,132 --> 00:17:56,313
You don't want to play if you really just want to go again.

326
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:58,934
You have the cash in button so you can just tap it,

327
00:17:59,714 --> 00:18:01,455
cash in your tokens, skip past it.

328
00:18:01,836 --> 00:18:04,277
All of these transitions you can tap on the screen

329
00:18:04,317 --> 00:18:06,398
and it will speed up or skip past them.

330
00:18:07,138 --> 00:18:08,459
And then we have the play again button

331
00:18:08,599 --> 00:18:10,720
which is in the bottom right hand corner and massive.

332
00:18:11,695 --> 00:18:15,018
And what you'll notice is the play again button is in the bottom right hand corner.

333
00:18:15,899 --> 00:18:20,683
So is the cash in button, so is the next button on the missions, so is the continue.

334
00:18:20,803 --> 00:18:24,406
Every button that involves you progressing is always in the bottom right hand corner.

335
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:29,771
And the main reason it's there is what we found is in playtesting was people were typically

336
00:18:29,831 --> 00:18:33,294
like around 80% of people were using the bottom right hand side of the screen.

337
00:18:33,794 --> 00:18:35,294
for actually putting in their input.

338
00:18:35,374 --> 00:18:36,915
Even though you can touch anywhere on the screen,

339
00:18:36,935 --> 00:18:39,836
the bottom right-hand screen is the preferred area.

340
00:18:40,436 --> 00:18:42,316
So every single thing in the game

341
00:18:42,396 --> 00:18:45,377
that involves you continuing or progressing to the next area

342
00:18:46,557 --> 00:18:47,938
is put in the bottom right-hand corner,

343
00:18:47,998 --> 00:18:50,478
and that way, even if you're not really paying attention,

344
00:18:50,498 --> 00:18:52,139
you're kind of playing and talking to someone,

345
00:18:52,379 --> 00:18:54,559
you just keep mashing the bottom right-hand side

346
00:18:54,579 --> 00:18:57,140
of the screen, you're gonna go to the next area,

347
00:18:57,420 --> 00:18:58,600
and you're gonna be able to restart.

348
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,742
So, testing.

