always, that's the one that comes to mind for me. And so what would happen is your

458
00:24:52,219 --> 00:24:55,861
intensity would be, you know, semi-low and then you would take a hit and it gets

459
00:24:55,941 --> 00:24:56,742
ratcheted right up

460
00:24:57,122 --> 00:25:00,404
and then it would come down again. And the weird thing here was the only way we could

461
00:25:00,444 --> 00:25:03,686
kind of kill the player, because we don't want the player to play for too long, remember?

462
00:25:04,026 --> 00:25:07,249
We need to keep our cost of failure in terms of time lost

463
00:25:07,429 --> 00:25:12,012
under control. It's to make the game extremely hard, you know, we're throwing

464
00:25:12,512 --> 00:25:16,114
millions of zappers at them so they take that second hit while they're in that state.

465
00:25:16,374 --> 00:25:17,635
So that didn't quite feel right either.

466
00:25:19,291 --> 00:25:20,112
So we'll come back to that.

467
00:25:21,432 --> 00:25:23,954
Problem two was variety. How do we add more variety?

468
00:25:24,194 --> 00:25:28,658
Well, we add variety in the same way that every other game in history has added variety.

469
00:25:29,478 --> 00:25:30,059
Power-ups.

470
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:34,222
And so we're coming up with these power-ups, and the problem is, is

471
00:25:35,122 --> 00:25:38,765
again, the game is so simple that we're really struggling to come up with power-ups.

472
00:25:38,805 --> 00:25:39,485
We have ones, you know...

473
00:25:39,993 --> 00:25:45,257
What are you going to do? You give Barry a shield, you make him invulnerable for a period of time,

474
00:25:45,697 --> 00:25:48,358
you slow down the game like a bullet time type thing,

475
00:25:50,540 --> 00:25:54,722
make the zappers smaller. I mean, you know, all these things kind of worked and they were

476
00:25:54,802 --> 00:25:56,884
interesting, but it was far from inspiring.

477
00:25:56,904 --> 00:25:59,885
It felt quite basic and wasn't quite there.

478
00:26:00,646 --> 00:26:05,148
So we're spending a long time bashing our heads against the wall, like, why is it so, so hard to

479
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:06,569
come up with power-ups for this game?

480
00:26:07,627 --> 00:26:09,989
So we had this idea of what if we change the controls?

481
00:26:10,629 --> 00:26:11,750
Maybe that's what we need to do.

482
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:14,672
People hate it when you change the controls, right?

483
00:26:14,772 --> 00:26:15,972
Because you die.

484
00:26:16,813 --> 00:26:18,874
You don't have enough time to get it figured out, and you die,

485
00:26:18,914 --> 00:26:22,136
and it feels really unfair and almost, like, disrespectful to the player.

486
00:26:23,417 --> 00:26:25,418
So this is where the idea of the vehicles came in.

487
00:26:25,738 --> 00:26:26,879
The idea of the vehicles is simple.

488
00:26:26,899 --> 00:26:29,721
We're going to change the controls, but we'll do it as a vehicle.

489
00:26:30,501 --> 00:26:33,563
And because it's a vehicle, you'll take the hit, you'll explode,

490
00:26:33,603 --> 00:26:34,724
but Barry will be okay.

491
00:26:35,264 --> 00:26:35,384
So...

492
00:26:36,413 --> 00:26:38,154
The controls are going to change, yes.

493
00:26:38,915 --> 00:26:40,256
But the thing is, it doesn't really matter.

494
00:26:40,276 --> 00:26:41,717
This is just a bonus run anyway.

495
00:26:41,737 --> 00:26:44,399
And because it was a bonus area and there was no real risk

496
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:47,342
to your overall game, we kind of felt like we could

497
00:26:48,103 --> 00:26:50,204
treat the player a little bit more disrespectfully

498
00:26:50,264 --> 00:26:52,466
in this time and make the assumption

499
00:26:52,506 --> 00:26:54,168
that they're going to die the first few times

500
00:26:54,208 --> 00:26:55,949
until they figure out how to use the vehicle.

501
00:26:58,553 --> 00:27:01,254
And all of a sudden the pacing completely changes for the game.

502
00:27:01,334 --> 00:27:04,996
Now it looks like this. It's always really intense still, like that very first graph.

503
00:27:05,456 --> 00:27:08,237
But when you get the vehicle, it drops way, way down.

504
00:27:08,917 --> 00:27:12,219
You're in a safe area, you've got this cool little variety moment,

505
00:27:12,239 --> 00:27:14,560
you know, the pacing has changed dramatically.

506
00:27:15,340 --> 00:27:19,362
Certainly, you know, while you're in the vehicle, the speed picks up and it does so quite quickly.

507
00:27:19,402 --> 00:27:21,983
We don't want you to spend too long in the vehicle,

508
00:27:22,483 --> 00:27:23,964
or else it's not going to be special anymore.

509
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:28,826
But you know, this really, you know, we were really excited about this.

510
00:27:28,866 --> 00:27:32,190
You know, the pacing was fixed, the variety was better.

511
00:27:32,822 --> 00:27:35,343
more explosions equals more beta, obviously.

512
00:27:35,623 --> 00:27:38,484
You can never have too many explosions in a game like this at least.

513
00:27:39,264 --> 00:27:41,925
And so, you know, we were feeling really, really good about this.

514
00:27:42,705 --> 00:27:44,386
It was definitely a big breakthrough for us.

515
00:27:44,906 --> 00:27:47,727
The other thing was the game had a big injection of character at this point,

516
00:27:47,747 --> 00:27:51,008
which is great, because before it was feeling a little bit dry and all that,

517
00:27:51,048 --> 00:27:52,789
and, you know, the Barry Steakfries universe,

518
00:27:52,869 --> 00:27:55,350
a game where the very first Barry Steakfries game,

519
00:27:56,090 --> 00:27:57,991
Age of Zombies, the opening line is,

520
00:27:58,131 --> 00:27:59,831
surprise, Professor Shit for Brains.

521
00:28:00,693 --> 00:28:03,874
really felt like it needed some extra character in it to, you know,

522
00:28:04,154 --> 00:28:05,714
make sense that it's Barry Steakfries.

523
00:28:06,634 --> 00:28:09,215
That said, you know, we kept everything much more G-rated this time.

524
00:28:11,035 --> 00:28:14,676
So then we're playing around with the vehicles and we're like, well, how dumb can we be?

525
00:28:15,036 --> 00:28:18,497
How crazy can we go? How stupid can these vehicles be

526
00:28:18,997 --> 00:28:22,898
before they're too dumb and too stupid and players don't like them?

527
00:28:24,740 --> 00:28:28,201
I'll concede as well, but not every player likes the crazy freaking teleporter.

528
00:28:28,641 --> 00:28:33,582
But this was our test, our foray into like, maybe we just come up with this really stupid

529
00:28:33,622 --> 00:28:37,684
bizarre, our original, I couldn't find a screenshot of it, the original prototype had this as

530
00:28:37,724 --> 00:28:40,945
the DeLorean for some reason with some really bad coder art on it.

531
00:28:41,585 --> 00:28:45,146
And this was us really testing the boundaries of the crazy stuff we could do.

532
00:28:45,226 --> 00:28:49,087
And you know, because it was wrapped in this bonus system and it was part of this world

533
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:53,648
that was kind of ridiculous, it all seemed to fit and you know, we didn't have any problems

534
00:28:53,688 --> 00:28:53,868
with it.

535
00:28:56,823 --> 00:29:00,004
So this kind of gets us to last year's GDC when we announced the game.

536
00:29:00,084 --> 00:29:03,746
It was the first time we'd done like a big playtest of the vehicle system,

537
00:29:04,246 --> 00:29:07,487
especially with external people that hadn't been there during the development of it.

538
00:29:08,127 --> 00:29:11,528
