00:29:18,910 --> 00:29:21,331
but we didn't anticipate to have, you know, what extent.

542
00:29:21,851 --> 00:29:23,412
People really did have difficulty with it.

543
00:29:24,652 --> 00:29:24,792
So...

544
00:29:25,608 --> 00:29:27,529
Again, more explosions.

545
00:29:27,989 --> 00:29:29,971
Explosions are the answer to all of our problems.

546
00:29:30,411 --> 00:29:32,392
When you pick up the vehicle, it explodes.

547
00:29:32,452 --> 00:29:35,174
There's a big doo-hoo, and it clears away all the obstacles.

548
00:29:35,214 --> 00:29:36,755
So this just gives you a bit of breathing room.

549
00:29:36,995 --> 00:29:39,497
Same when you destroy the vehicle.

550
00:29:39,637 --> 00:29:40,938
I mean, that worked to an extent.

551
00:29:40,958 --> 00:29:41,859
That worked OK.

552
00:29:42,599 --> 00:29:46,842
But where we really, really found ourselves breaking through

553
00:29:46,862 --> 00:29:49,223
was when we started mucking around with these kind

554
00:29:49,263 --> 00:29:50,864
of scripted coin sequences.

555
00:29:51,365 --> 00:29:53,086
So the first time you pick up a vehicle,

556
00:29:53,910 --> 00:29:57,920
Well, sorry, every time you pick up a vehicle, no matter what, you get two sequences of coins.

557
00:29:59,103 --> 00:30:00,125
And what these coins do is...

558
00:30:01,275 --> 00:30:05,719
they're never on the ground, they're never where you can get them without having to do something.

559
00:30:06,359 --> 00:30:08,981
So it really provides the player with a goal

560
00:30:09,482 --> 00:30:12,704
and something that, you know, they're not going to get it just by watching the game play out.

561
00:30:12,784 --> 00:30:15,486
They're going to see this goal and they're going to have to figure out how to get there.

562
00:30:15,506 --> 00:30:19,729
So it acts like this little kind of mini tutorial time and we do it every single time.

563
00:30:20,170 --> 00:30:23,552
Because, you know, there's six vehicles and you've got the jetpack as well,

564
00:30:24,393 --> 00:30:28,056
seven control schemes to keep track of, this control...

565
00:30:28,076 --> 00:30:30,637
Sorry, this playground area almost.

566
00:30:31,515 --> 00:30:35,199
really gives the player a chance to explore the controls and get familiar with them again,

567
00:30:35,279 --> 00:30:36,680
get recalibrated with them again.

568
00:30:37,141 --> 00:30:41,645
You might remember how it works but you might not quite remember how it feels, how quickly

569
00:30:41,685 --> 00:30:45,549
the gravity changes, how quickly you can press it again.

570
00:30:46,469 --> 00:30:51,895
Also when the vehicle explodes we add another coin sequence again, and this gives you another

571
00:30:52,055 --> 00:30:55,298
kind of little section of time to get recalibrated and kind of re-buried.

572
00:30:57,719 --> 00:31:00,041
The number of vehicles is kind of an interesting thing as well.

573
00:31:00,601 --> 00:31:04,363
Because these vehicles have so much kind of character and they all control really differently,

574
00:31:04,764 --> 00:31:06,064
everyone has their favorite, right?

