00:31:06,104 --> 00:31:08,506
Like, people really latch on to what their favorite one is.

576
00:31:09,667 --> 00:31:13,009
The balance here is, if you have too few vehicles,

577
00:31:13,729 --> 00:31:18,412
you are getting your favorite one so often that it doesn't feel special and that you're not excited.

578
00:31:19,213 --> 00:31:22,215
Too many vehicles, you're not getting your favorite one often enough.

579
00:31:23,460 --> 00:31:27,663
So we always found, you know, we have a similar amount of weapons in Monster Dash.

580
00:31:27,683 --> 00:31:31,325
We really felt like around six or maybe seven was the sweet spot.

581
00:31:31,786 --> 00:31:34,968
Where, you know, when you get your favorite one, so the favorite one for me is always

582
00:31:35,128 --> 00:31:35,748
Little Stomper.

583
00:31:35,808 --> 00:31:38,370
When I get him I'm excited and I'm like, yeah, Little Stomper time.

584
00:31:40,554 --> 00:31:57,364
So yeah, it was really important. There's some other interesting things to do with the way that, you know, we had to mess around with the probability of the vehicles in the missions, because when you have a mission that's like, you know, you need little stomper for something, it kind of dramatically changes your perception of how often it comes up.

585
00:31:57,865 --> 00:32:01,828
because you go, you collect like four vehicles and not get the stomper and in your mind you're

586
00:32:01,848 --> 00:32:05,952
saying god damn it the stomper never ever spawns even though it's well within the realms

587
00:32:05,992 --> 00:32:07,933
of like you know standard probability.

588
00:32:08,154 --> 00:32:12,778
So we actually kind of game it at that point and override the probability if you haven't

589
00:32:12,818 --> 00:32:15,760
gotten the vehicle you need to complete a mission in a long time.

590
00:32:16,161 --> 00:32:17,962
A long time, it's like three pickups.

